---
description: Apply TDD and testing best practices with Vitest. Use when creating or modifying test files.
globs: **/*.test.ts,**/*.spec.ts,**/__tests__/**/*.ts,**/vitest.config.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

TDD Approach (ADR-014):

- Write failing test FIRST
- Write minimum code to pass
- Refactor while tests stay green

Test Framework — Vitest 3.x:

- Config per app: `vitest.config.ts`
- Run via Docker: `docker compose exec {service} bun run test`
- Use `describe`, `it`, `expect`, `vi.fn()`, `vi.spyOn()`
- `vi.mock()` for module mocking, `vi.fn()` for port/interface mocking
- `beforeEach(() => vi.clearAllMocks())` to reset between tests

Test Organization:

- Unit tests: `src/__tests__/unit/` or co-located `__tests__/` folders
- Route tests: `src/__tests__/unit/routes/` (Hono `app.request()`)
- Integration tests: `test/integration/` per app
- E2E tests: `test/e2e/` per app

Hexagonal Testing:

- Domain entities: pure unit tests, no mocks needed
- Use cases: mock ports (interfaces) via `vi.fn()` implementing the port interface
- Adapters: integration tests against real services (Prisma, Redis) in Docker
- Routes: use Hono's `app.request()` with mocked use cases (no supertest needed)

Naming:

- `describe('ClassName')` or `describe('use-case-name')`
- `it('should [expected behavior] when [condition]')`

Assertions:

- Use AAA pattern: Arrange, Act, Assert
- One assertion focus per test (can have multiple related asserts)
- Test both happy path AND error cases

Anti-Patterns:

- Never write tests after implementation
- Never mock internal modules — only mock at boundaries (ports)
- Never test implementation details — test behavior
- Never skip edge cases in coverage
- Never use `jest` — project uses Vitest exclusively
